ISW (Infi Systems Widgets) - XCB-based 3D Widget Library
==========================================================

ISW is a modern fork of the X 3D Athena Widget Set (Isw3d), featuring:
- Native XCB (X protocol C-language Binding) rendering support
- Enhanced 3D visual effects with shadow and lighting
- Arrow scrollbars for improved usability
- Full internationalization support
- Xft font rendering with anti-aliasing

This library is based on the X Toolkit Intrinsics (Xt) Library and provides
a comprehensive set of widgets for building X11 graphical user interfaces.

FEATURES
--------
- Modern XCB rendering backend for better performance
- 3D-styled widgets with configurable shadows and bevels
- Arrow controls on scrollbars (configurable)
- Multi-language text support with XIM integration
- Anti-aliased text rendering via Xft
- Compatible with existing Xt-based applications

BUILDING
--------
See BUILD_INSTRUCTIONS.md for detailed build instructions.

Quick start:
    ./autogen.sh
    ./configure --enable-arrow-scrollbars --enable-internationalization
    make
    sudo make install

FORKED FROM
-----------
This project is a modernized fork of Isw3d (X 3D Athena Widget Set).
Original Isw3d repository:
    git://anongit.freedesktop.org/git/xorg/lib/libIsw3d

